### ||| غزوه ذات الرقاع SEE_TBRBV02P555B

# @TBRBV02P555C_BEG_WSFAB فقال ابن إسحاق في ذلك ما حدثنا @TR2_MIHD@ ابن حميد قال حدثنا @TR1_SFAB@ سلمة قال حدثنا محمد بن إسحاق قال ثم اقام رسول الله صلى الله عليه وسلم بالمدينة بعد غزوة بني النضير شهري ربيع وبعض شهر جمادى ثم غزا نجدا يريد بني محارب وبني ثعلبة من غطفان حتى PageV02P555 نزل نخلا وهي غزوة ذات الرقاع فلقي بها جمعا من غطفان فتقارب الناس ولم يكن بينهم حرب وقد خاف الناس بعضهم بعضا حتى صلى رسول الله صلى الله عليه وسلم بالمسلمين صلاة الخوف ثم انصرف بالمسلمين. @TBRBV02P555C_END_WSFAB
PageV02P556
# @COMMENT: These passages refer to the "fear prayer" (صلاة الخوف) that in WZATB occurs, in the redaction of Ibn Hishām on HSNXV02P204D just before the expedition to Dhāt al-Riqāʿ in the year 4. Quotations that deal with the events surrounding the fear prayer are also found in WZATB on DHTIV02P249C and HJRQV04P116F but these quotations are not complete and only include elements of the story. Fragments on the fear prayer are also found in WSFAB on TBRBV02P555C, TBRBV02P556B, and in BQSXV03P375A. In WZATB no sources are mentioned that provide any clue as to the origins of the account. In the WSFAB account found in al-Ṭabarī the source is listed as Muḥammad b. ʿAbd al-Raḥmān  b. Nawfal b. al-Aswad. BQSXV03P375A lists two sources, Muḥammad b. ʿAbd al-Raḥmān  b. Nawfal b. al-Aswad and Muḥammad b. Jaʿfar  b. al-Zubayr b. al-ʿAwwām, although al-Bayhaqī does not say much about how, or if, these two sources present differing views.  WYBWS provides variations of the Muḥammad b. Jaʿfar  b. al-Zubayr traditions on ZZBXV14P347B and THSMV01P314B. al-Bayhaqī includes a mention of WYBWS in his account mentioned above saying that Ibn Bukayr includes accounts from both Muḥammad b. Jaʿfar and Muḥammad b. ʿAbd al-Raḥmān without providing any details. WSACD provides the most diverse collection of stories on the fear prayer, listing traditions from an unknown source (HJRQV04P116F), Muḥammad b. ʿAbd al-Raḥmān  b. Nawfal b. al-Aswad (KHZXV02P301B and HYZXV01P153F), Muḥammad b. Jaʿfar (HBHXV43P373B, KHZXV02P303B, BNIBV07P124B, NSSXV01P487A, BQSXV03P375A, BQSXV03P376B, and HYZXV01P154E), and from Dāwūd b. al-Ḥuṣayn, a mawlā of ʿAmr b. ʿUthmān (HBHXV04P212A, ANSSV03P170A, NSKXV02P367A, and BQSXV03P367D). There are also several unwitnessed versions in the corpus via Dāwūd b. al-Ḥuṣayn (RJSBV08P366B, IMBTV05P014C and HJTHV02P181B, who quotes al-Bayhaqī). In the WSACD collection, the passages are grouped by source for comparison. @EC_12/20/23@

